1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Temaşevanên hêja, vê hefteyê jî me berê xwe da gundê Stêr.
 
Dear viewers, this week we headed to the village of Ster.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Ev gundê Stêr jî girêdayî navenda Efrînê ye. Gundekî gelek
xweş e. Derdora vê gundî hemî av e.
 
The village of Ster is also connected to the center of
Afrin. It is a very beautiful village. This village is
surrounded by water.

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Ev gund berê yek kurê reş îd bû, dema sîstema Sûriyê
biryarek derxist mîlkê axleran bela kir,
 
This village used to belong to one man, then the Syrian
system issued a decree and distributed the properties of the
landlords,

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:41,000
di wê demê de Kurd û Ereb derbasî vê gundî bûn, naha ev gund
jî Kurd û Ereb bi hev re jiyan dikin. De ka vê hefteyê jî em
derbasî vê gundî bibin.
 
at that time Kurds and Arabs entered this village, now Kurds
and Arabs live together in this village. Let's go into this
village this week.

5
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:57,000
Belê, temaşevanên me yên hêja, em derbasî gundê Stêr bûn,
 
Yes, dear viewers, we have entered the village of Ster,

6
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,000
em hatin jî li bin darên tûyan rûniştin,
 
we came and sat under the mulberry trees,

7
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Gundî jî hatin derdora me; bi Kurd û Erebên xwe.
 
The villagers also gathered around us; both Kurds and Arabs.

8
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,000
Em ê bipirsin dîroka gund.
 
We will ask about the history of the village.

9
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:10,000
Li ser milê min î rastê apê Beyrem, li ser milê min î çepê
jî apê Elî ye.
 
On my right is Uncle Bayram, on my left is Uncle Ali.

10
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
Yek Kurd e yek Ereb e, em ê dîroka gund ji wan bipirsin.
 
One is Kurdish, one is Arab, we will ask them the history of
the village.

11
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Merheba ji we re Apê Beyrem.
 
Hello to you, Uncle Bayram.

12
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:16,000
Ahlan wa sahlan.
 
Welcome.

13
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
Bûyur çê pirsê te heye li ser serê min.
 
Please, whatever questions you have, I'm at your service.

14
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Sax bî, Apê Beyrem, ev gundê Stêr çi qas sal e çêbûye?
 
Thank you, Uncle Bayram, how many years has this village of
Ster been established?

15
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Ev gundê Stêr, teqrîben nod û pênc, nod û şeş, nod û heft...
di wî dorê de ye yanî...
 
This village of Ster, approximately 95, 96, 97... it's
around that time...

16
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Gundê me berê li wêrê bû, gundê me berê Qilbê Mehetê bû,
 
Our village used to be there, our village used to be Qilbe
Mehete,

17
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
ango di bin erdê Xirabê Lo derê bû.
 
meaning it was below the lands of Xirabe Lo dere.

18
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Dûrî vir e?
 
Is it far from here?

19
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Sê çar kîlometre heye yanî... pênc kîlometre heye, şemalî me
ye, Qilbê Mehetê ye...
 
It is three or four kilometers... maybe five kilometers
away, to our north, Qilbe Mehete...

20
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:50,000
Paşê, jê û derê gund û.. milet jê çû yanî... ku reş îd bi
tenê ma.
 
Then, the village over there and... people left it... only
Kur Reşid remained.

21
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Ew gund mezin bû li wê derê?
 
Was that village big over there?

22
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Çar pênc mal bûn yanî.. ne zêde bû.
 
There were four or five households... it wasn't much.

23
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Paşê, Kur Reşid hat li vir çêkir, vir hawayên bilind e,
ehtîbar yanî cihekî xweş e, dorê wê kaniyên avê ne,
 
Then, Kur Reşid came and built here, here the weather is
high, reliable, meaning it's a beautiful place, surrounded
by water springs,

24
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,000
zeriya wî ye, hat li vir qonaxê girt.
 
his farmland, he came here and set up residence.

25
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:03,000
Li wê derê av tune ye?
 
Is there no water over there?

26
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:08,000
Av heye li dûr e, avê Efrînê, nedihat vê xwarê yanî.
Berrê...
 
There is water but it's far, the Afrin water, it didn't flow
down here. Previously...

27
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Av çênabû, meqbaza derê tabe dibû, we ne hate xwarê. Kaniyê
li dorê me nêzîk in e,
 
The water couldn't reach, the catch basin over there was
attached, it didn't come down. The springs are near us,

28
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,000
gund hat li vir amirandin, li vir e girt.
 
the village was established here, he took it here.

29
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:17,000
Paşê cûteyarî gund da hatin...
 
Then the sharecroppers came to the village...

30
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Yanî Kur Reşid ji wê derê rabû hat li vir e?
 
So Kur Reşid got up from there and came here?

31
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Hat li vir e, dîwanekî mezin li vir çêkir...
 
He came here, he built a large guest house here...

32
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Cotarî jî hemî bi wî re hatin li vir?
 
Did all the sharecroppers come here with him?

33
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Hat li vir e... û paşê em ko werin...
 
He came here... and later when we came...

34
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
Em hatin, em bûn çar pênc mal yanî.
 
We came, we became four or five households.

35
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Em hatin, dorê cotarî...
 
We came, around the sharecroppers...

36
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Ereb jî wê demê hebûn an tune bûn?
 
Were there Arabs at that time or not?

37
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:36,000
Çar pênc mal Ereb jê hatin cem me. Badî fetra (piştî demekê)
kî, pênc şeş sala...
 
Four or five Arab households also came to us. After a while,
five or six years...

38
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Hawc hatin, em bûn, teqrîben dehe mal; kurmanc bi hev re. Em
bi hev re mezin bûn yanî.
 
They came, we became, approximately ten households; Kurds
together. We grew up together.

39
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:46,000
Ji zarokatiya xwe de. Em bi hev re mezin bûn... em jê bûn,
bi wan tinne...
 
From our childhood. We grew up together... we became
separated from them, no...

40
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:48,000
Em jê ji hev nerazî nebûn...
 
We were never displeased with one another...

41
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:54,000
Û paşê hinekan yekî meselen ji Qestelê hatin, hinek ji
Me'milê hatin, hinek ji Gêçiya hatin, hinek ji Gemrûkê
hatin,
 
And later some, for example one came from Qestel, some from
Ma'mil, some from Gechiya, some from Gemruk,

42
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
mûcteme'ê gund mezin bû. Gund ji gund çêbû.
 
the community of the village grew. A village grew out of a
village.

43
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Qickî qicko dewet kirin, gund mezin bû.
 
Gradually, weddings were held, the village grew.

44
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Belê gundî me naha çend malan e teqrîben?
 
Yes, approximately how many households is our village now?

45
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Gundî me naha haliyen, heftê û pênc, heftê û şeş, dore heştê
ye.
 
Our village currently is 75, 76, around 80.

46
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:09,000
Hinek jê, hinek Erebin jê batmaleb da.. bêtûşim bin. Ev jêrê
gundî me ye.
 
Some of them, some are Arabs... I'm not sure. That's below
our village.

47
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,000
Yanî tu dikarê bêjê dore heştê malê heye.
 
In other words, you can say there are around 80 households.

48
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Yanî li vir av hebe, ji ber wê avê hemî hatin...
 
Meaning since there's water here, they all came because of
the water...

49
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:19,000
Ji ber wê avê hatibûn. Berê, yardimiya xwe jê rind e. Dorî
xwe ferah e jê.
 
They came because of the water. Earlier, its help was good.
Its surroundings are spacious too.

50
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:24,000
Û, hawayê xwe heye... yanî tiştî rind e yanî.
 
And, it has good weather... so it's a good thing.

51
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:30,000
Û zeriya xwe, av... meselen, av Efrîn bê... wî derê, kaniya
da derê, dorê... dû şerê me av e.
 
And its farming, water... for example, the water of Afrin
comes... over there, from the spring, around... behind our
village is water.

52
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:34,000
Heta vê... gelyê... dehe derhekî.. qiçkê hejde salî nehwre..
xul xiste..
 
Up until this... valley... around ten... a small boy of 18
years over there... got in..

53
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,000
Vê derê wî geliyê ho, naha hişk bûye.
 
Right here, this valley over there, it has dried up now.

54
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:41,000
Û zirafokî kelekî.. ma ev av e... yanî dorê me giş av e, giş
ziraat e.
 
And farming a bit.. is this water... so our surroundings are
all water, all agriculture.

55
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,000
Wê demê ne didan...
 
At that time they weren't giving...

56
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Pembû û baxçê diçandin.
 
They were planting cotton and orchards.

57
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:50,000
Yanî kes, kêm pace û tayê, şivan der der.. tiştên holê na...
diçandin. Nezanîn...
 
Nobody... there were few shepherds... they didn't plant such
things. Ignorance...

58
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:52,000
Şivandar kî ko.. vê mantiqînî.. yekî Emîrût e.
 
Those shepherds who... this area... one of the Emirut.

59
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:58,000
Ehmed Cebelî... navî... ewî şivandar ê vê mantiqê xist...
bir da xist. Şiketa... şiketa kura ye.
 
Ahmed Jebeli... his name... he brought sheep herding to this
area... brought it. To Shiketa... deep Shiketa.

60
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:02,000
Li vir çand, înteşa wî ra rind bû... û milet jê elmî.
 
Planted here, his yield was good... and the people learned
from him.

61
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:08,000
Wî çand, ê din çand, cotarî giş axirda fetilîn giş şivandera
çandin... şivanderî piser ket...
 
He planted, the other planted, all the farmers eventually
turned to planting sugar beets... sugar beets became
widespread...

62
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:14,000
Û paşê şiv... du sê sala şivandar de'wî xurmir. Orda pembû
jî de'wî xurmir.
 
And then later... after two or three years sugar beet yields
dropped. Then cotton yields dropped too.

63
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:16,000
Paşê e pere pozê xistin tiştên...
 
Later they directed money towards things...

64
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:22,000
Paşê tiştê honî kî, baxçê diçînin, zebeş, gundir, xeyar,
falan bê honî... em wan tiştan diçînin.
 
Like orchards they plant, watermelons, melons, cucumbers, so
on and so forth... we plant those things.

65
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Gûnd jî.. naha elhemduleh.. vir re, berê gundê me.. li vir
bû.. ji vir, tehwîl we da bû.
 
The village also... now thank God... here, before our
village... was here... from here, it transferred.

66
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Ne.. ku derê...
 
Where to...

67
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:32,000
Ew dorê hewşê we da bûn.
 
They were around the courtyards over there.

68
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:34,000
Yanî piştî we cuhur hate vir.. ev gund bû.
 
So after the water came here... this village was formed.

69
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
Paşê em tehwîlê olî bûn. Teqrîben bîst... pênc..
 
Later we relocated up high. Approximately 20... 5..

70
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Na.. gund mezin bûye?
 
Has the village grown?

71
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:43,000
Bîst û pênc sal ha... em tehwîlê we da bûn e. Bes naha gund
mezin bûye. Gund teqrîbe defsilî de ji hev bûro...
 
It's been 25 years... since we relocated there. But now the
village has grown. The village essentially separated from
each other...

72
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Yanî zarok mezin bûn... û zewicandin.
 
Meaning the children grew up... and got married.

73
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,000
Lê, qiçkê.. qiçko zawicîn yorto...
 
Yes, the little... little ones got married...

74
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:53,000
Mezin bû... mal fireh bû, maşaleh. Her derî zêde dibe, ew
hemî Xwedê kî zêde bike...
 
It grew... families expanded, Mashallah. Everywhere is
increasing, may God increase it all...

75
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Sax bî, ne miletê tê vir re, giş gundan e tê ne...
 
Stay healthy, so the people who come here, they all come
from the villages...

76
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Giş gundan hatine.
 
They've come from all the villages.

77
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,000
Piraniyek kîjan gundan hatine?
 
Most have come from which villages?

78
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:04,000
Ê pirr... eh piran... eh... malbata piran naha ko ji Me'milê
ye.
 
The most... the most... the biggest family now is from
Me'mil.

79
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,000
Ji Gundê Me'milê berê xwe dane vir.
 
They came here from the village of Me'mil.

80
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Hatin malek bû.. û berê ko.. ji porî bû şeş heft bera kon..
 
They came, it was one household... and earlier... they grew
to six or seven households...

81
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,000
Te ji kuderê?
 
Where are you from?

82
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Ez ji, ji Efrînê bûm.
 
I am, I was from Afrin.

83
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:16,000
Yanê.. beriya Kur Reşid, bav û kiyê min... li qoltola qey...
paşê hat efrîn ji wêr jî em hatin vir e.
 
I mean... before Kur Reşid, my father and grandfather... in
Qoltola maybe... then came to Afrin and from there we came
here.

84
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Û piraniya, malbatên din jî, ji kuderê hatine?
 
And the majority, the other families, where have they come
from?

85
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,000
Malbatê din jî hine..k ji Qestelê hatin.
 
The other families... some came from Qestel.

86
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:23,000
Hinek.. ji seri... ji Kaniyê hatin.
 
Some... from above... from the spring.

87
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,000
Û hinek.. ji Efrînê hatin. Û hinek, ji Gemrûkê hatin.
 
And some... came from Afrin. And some, from Gemruk.

88
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
Yane.. mal, her cihekî... derketiye.
 
So... households, from every place... they have emerged.

89
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Belê gundekî tevlî hev bûye.
 
Yes, it's become a mixed village.

90
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:34,000
Me gund ku.. tevlî hev çêker... em giş tevbûne... em bihevre
daxişin yanî...
 
The village has... become mixed... we've all integrated...
we live together...

91
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,000
Em fihlen jî... e me yeke... destê me yeke.
 
Truly we are... we are one... our hand is one.

92
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Elhemdule... kesî.. ji kesî.. vir da wê da... bi fesa diyo..
nerdiyo... te neye..
 
Thank God... no one... to anyone... back and forth... with
malice... doesn't happen... it's not there...

93
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,000
Em gih bra ko... evan...
 
We are all brothers... this...

94
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Em ko nesey.. ko ser sofrokê ko... nan ji dixwe..
 
If we don't... sit at the table... eating bread together...

95
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,000
Û gihi.. bi hev ray... elhamdulileh... Em giş brawko...
evin...
 
And all... with each other... thank God... We are all
brothers... together...

96
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,000
Ev jî nîmetekî...
 
This is also a blessing...

97
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:50,000
Nîmetekî.. nîmetekî mezine...
 
A blessing... a great blessing...

98
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Spas darim ka em ê bi te... Apê Elî jî bipirsin...
 
Thank you, let us also ask... Uncle Ali.

99
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Apê Elî, merhaba.
 
Uncle Ali, hello.

100
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Ehlên, merhaba.
 
Welcome, hello.

101
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:57,000
Em biterê Kurmancî bi axifin yê erebî?
 
Should we speak to you in Kurmanji or Arabic?

102
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:59,000
Ferq nake.. Kurmancî mir dinike..
 
It doesn't matter... Kurmanji is fine for me.

103
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,000
Tu kurmancî rind dizane?
 
You know Kurmanji well?

104
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,000
Apê Elî...
 
Uncle Ali...

105
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Vê malê ereb bu.. çend malin li vir na?
 
This Arab household... how many households are there here?

106
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,000
Welle na ko.. nîv e bi nîv e...
 
Well right now... it's half and half...

107
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:11,000
Yane... weke... apê Bayram qehse kir...
 
I mean... as... Uncle Bayram talked about...

108
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:18,000
Yane, apê Bayram bicûz, tiştekî pîrbikir... ba... ez,
bizakirî min... liannu... cem me.. malê me li Efrîn in.
 
I mean, Uncle Bayram maybe missed something... because... I,
to my knowledge... because... for us... our homes are in
Afrin.

109
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:23,000
Ji go.. em derketin... ji Efrîn... balke... mal.. hişti bin
saredi jî..
 
Since... we left... from Afrin... maybe... homes... we might
have left above as well..

110
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:29,000
Mal... mehtemil kuştî saredi jî... mesela, te.. derketin..
Efrîn. Çend mal... min... el Efrîne ne.
 
Homes... possibly they stayed above too... for example,
you... left... Afrin. How many households... I... the ones
from Afrin...

111
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:33,000
Hinik li Helebê hinik.. derve welat... hewş digrin.. bi giş
bibrin.. bi ser..
 
Some in Aleppo, some... abroad... they build houses... they
take all... above...

112
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:36,000
E.. Hun ji, çiqa saliye hatin, vir ro?
 
Uh... And you, how many years ago did you come here?

113
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:43,000
Welle emrê min.. gihîştî şêst e... teqrîben az, çar sali..
pênc sali bum. Dor sî û çaro... em xotin vir..
 
Well my age... has reached sixty... approximately I was,
four years... five years old. Around 34... we came here..

114
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Bes marazim tu bi Erebî.. kurdiya te pirbaş e..
 
Only I want you in Arabic.. your Kurdish is very good..

115
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:48,000
Vir.. Erebî.. gamurk eçe bêm e.
 
Here.. Arabic.. the customs post went.

116
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:51,000
Mari me... E.. me xwe, xwe di helzewci.. ye..
 
Our guys... uh.. we got married..

117
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,000
Bate men. Kurmancin. Meselen.
 
My daughters. They are Kurds. For example.

118
00:06:53,000 --> 00:07:01,000
Em berê me, gihîştî ev derê... bi rîu. Na ko em gihîşt ev
der... diyo û stûniya. Mesela, xelkê me... birinim. Me jê...
berene. Yane..
 
Since the past, we have arrived here... on the road. Now we
have arrived here... standing. For example, our people...
took them. We also... gave. I mean..

119
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:04,000
Geyi biniye... waqe gutiya.. a muqebara kab e diro.. masun
bine..
 
It's all the foundation... as he said... until we grow
old... they will remain..

120
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,000
Kurdî ereb, bo sehsala... bi hazar salab hev rajiya..
 
Kurds, Arabs, for hundreds of years... thousands of years
living together..

121
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:13,000
Ba sehsala... we ni... am nezunin tiş çaw wext otin u.. em
nezinin yani vê.. tarixan, am nezunin...
 
With hundreds of years... that.. we don't know when they
came and.. we don't know, meaning this.. history, we don't
know...

122
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,000
Yane dide ji berda kurd û ereb jêrînan ha bi tirik jiyan.
 
Meaning since before Kurds and Arabs lived together down
there with Turks.

123
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:23,000
Bi hevre, am eyşan na jiyan, de ber da, ne jihiroda na.. am
nezunene ciqas da tarîxe kî kasan nizane. Am nêzanîn yaw
na...
 
Together, we lived our lives, before, neither from below..
we don't know how much history nobody knows. We don't know,
man..

124
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:30,000
Ço wext.. a. Bas e mehve dê re masin be nu. Ba fqê me me.
Bav de re masin bîne. Kolk de men bav da re masin bînu.
Kolk... me din.. bav dera nu we go...
 
At what time.. yeah. But we grew up here. With my
understanding. We grew up here with our fathers. My people
grew up here with our fathers. Our people... gave.. came
here and...

125
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Çiqas tiştekî ba şe. Yane Kurdî ereb. Herdum xeman hev
dizanin ba...
 
What a good thing. Meaning Kurds and Arabs. Both know each
other's troubles...

126
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,000
E tab'an.
 
Of course.

127
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Ev go bi zarokî.. na hev dixafen e.
 
The one who as a child.. now speaks with each other.

128
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:37,000
E. Me na gihşt zanu ve.. na gor num aşa.
 
Yes. We didn't reach knowing this.. now I don't see
anything.

129
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:39,000
Na ta.. tu berek xos tu axufe. Le bir Kurmancî..
 
Now you.. you speak for yourself. But in Kurmanji..

130
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Tu num.. Kirmonci...
 
You're not.. Kurmanji...

131
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,000
Kirmonci baş diaxife.
 
He speaks Kurmanji well.

132
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,000
Gund kî hemu wasa ba kirmoncî bi axivn.
 
The village all speak Kurmanji like this.

133
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,000
Vaye yê Ereb jê hemî bi kurmancî dizanin.
 
See, all the Arabs also know Kurmanji.

134
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:50,000
Iyla.. hek.. qismek basît.. bi mesela heta bura jinen ereb
bo me ye... kirmonci..
 
Except.. a simple part.. for example even Arab women came
here... Kurmanji..

135
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,000
E Apê Elî emê tişan da xwen re... E... emê ji ra b... spas
dar in.
 
Ah Uncle Ali we will see ourselves to some things... Uh...
we... are thankful to you.

136
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:55,000
Ehlen wu sehlen fî kum
 
Welcome to you.

137
00:07:55,000 --> 00:08:00,000
Xodeta wa efuqek wo wezda viki.
 
May God extend your life and increase it.

138
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:02,000
E sedit sedih xos xos wene.
 
One hundred times welcome to you.

139
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:08,000
Gundê Stêr, yek ji gundên navçeya Mabata ya Efrînê ye.
 
The village of Ster is one of the villages in the Mabata
district of Afrin.

140
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:11,000
Û pênc kîlometrî bakurê bajarê Efrînê dikeve.
 
And it is located five kilometers north of the city of
Afrin.

141
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:14,000
Gund li ser kenarê Çemê Efrînê dida çuqiyed e.
 
The village is nestled on the edge of the Afrin River.

142
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:20,000
Beriya nêzî sedsalî, ji aliyê pênc malbatan ve hatiye
avakirin.
 
Nearly a century ago, it was established by five families.

143
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:26,000
Yek ji malbatên destpêkê, malbata Kur Reşîd bû. Di herêmê de
gelek navdar e.
 
One of the first families was the Kur Reshid family. Very
famous in the region.

144
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:34,000
Rêjîma Baasê bi Qanûna Reş a Reform a Çandiniyê, ango îslaha
zîraî, hewl da ku demografiya herêmê biguhêre.
 
The Ba'ath regime, through the Black Law of Agricultural
Reform, or Islah al-Zira'i, attempted to change the region's
demographics.

145
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:41,000
Rêjîmê di gundî de jî, di çarçoveya vê qanûnê de gelek caran
hewl da siyasetên dîvîrengî bi da meşandin.
 
The regime also frequently tried to implement multi-colored
policies in this village within the framework of this law.

146
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:49,000
Lê bi saya hevkirina Kurd û Ereban gund ev siyaseta baasê
têk çû.
 
But thanks to the unity of the Kurds and Arabs in the
village, this Ba'ath policy was defeated.

147
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja,
 
Yes, our esteemed viewers,

148
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Em rastî zarokan jî hatin.
 
We also came across children.

149
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,000
Zarok jî lîstikeke xwe dilîzin.
 
The children are playing a game.

150
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Zarok hin Kurd in hin jî Ereb in.
 
Some of the children are Kurds and some are Arabs.

151
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
Hemî bi hev re lîstikê xwe dilîzin. Niha em bipirsin;
 
They are all playing their games together. Now let's ask;

152
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:02,000
Navê te çiye û lîstika wan çiye. Merheba zaro!
 
What's your name and what is their game. Hello kid!

153
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:03,000
Ehlên, ya Xal.
 
Welcome, uncle.

154
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,000
Navê te çiye?
 
What is your name?

155
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,000
Azad.
 
Azad.

156
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Yê te?
 
And yours?

157
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Kîja ji we Kurd e, kîja Ereb e?
 
Mustafa.

158
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:08,000
Kîja ji we Kurd e, kîja Ereb e?
 
Which of you is Kurdish, which is Arab?

159
00:09:08,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Hamê Arabo u hav arab e.. wih.. haf u haf u haf arab...
(mixed voices)
 
All Arabs and this is Arab.. that.. this and this and this
is Arab...

160
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,000
Tu Ereb î?
 
You are Arab?

161
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:13,000
Tu bi Kurmancî zanî, te ba xife deng ke..
 
Yes.

162
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:16,000
Tu bi Kurmancî zanî, te ba xife deng ke..
 
You know Kurmanji, speak a little louder..

163
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:17,000
Ha...
 
Yes...

164
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:19,000
Mirovê me.. E... erebo..
 
Our guy.. uh... is Arab..

165
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,000
Niha lîstika we çiye?
 
Now what is your game?

166
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:23,000
E... Teqlîs e..
 
Uh... It's Teqlis (Marbles)..

167
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:27,000
Da serê êk ev kinê... Çepşortan e ka ye. Em dilîzin.
 
On top of each other... It is like marbles. We play.

168
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Em ê bilîzin na ko... no... em bilîzin!
 
We will play now... here... let's play!

169
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,000
Eme teqlîz bilîzin.
 
We are playing marbles.

170
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,000
Hûn çend kes dilîzin?
 
How many of you play?

171
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,000
Em pirr dilîzin.
 
We play a lot.

172
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:39,000
Em hav dlizin hav hav hav em kî dlîz.. iye zane em dlizin...
 
We play this this this this we who plays.. who knows we
play...

173
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,000
Yane em li gî dinêşin...
 
So we don't all look...

174
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:44,000
Na... Hinek piçûkin. Nemaş in.
 
No... Some are small. They don't play.

175
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,000
Teqlîz hûn çawa dilîzin, ka ji min re bêje.
 
How do you play marbles, tell me.

176
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Teqlîs yeke dî ser yekê kê yeke bigire dibe teqlîs.
 
Marbles, one on top of the other, if one hits it becomes
marbles.

177
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:52,000
Diskine, nemaşe uvekê.. Dar ê.
 
He hits it, he doesn't play with it.. Wood.

178
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:57,000
Vedikê... dizî xwu nali teke dbe meftûx vade ke.
 
He opens... he takes it himself, he gets the open one.

179
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Paşî di sê ro vê.. wî moken do dî de dî me.
 
Then tomorrow this.. that place will give it back to us.

180
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:04,000
Dersa te çi ye? Tê dizanibî bibêjî? Ha? Erê?
 
What is your subject? Will you be able to recite it? Huh?
Yes?

181
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,000
Tê herî mektebê, diçî dibistanê?
 
You go to school, you go to school?

182
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

183
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:08,000
Refa çendî dixwînî, refa çendî?
 
Which grade are you in, which grade?

184
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Heftê.
 
Seventh.

185
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:10,000
Erê.
 
Seventh?

186
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

187
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,000
Tê bi Kurmancî dixwînî?
 
Do you study in Kurmanji?

188
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,000
Bi Erebî.
 
In Arabic.

189
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,000
Ha, bi Erebî?
 
Oh, in Arabic?

190
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

191
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,000
Ka navê xwe bêje ne, tê helbestekê bêjî ne? Te helbestekê...
 
Come on, tell us your name, you're going to recite a poem,
right? You have a poem...

192
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:18,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

193
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:20,000
De ka... Navê xwe bêje... Kî derê... tê ji me ra li vir
bibêjî ne?
 
Come on... Tell us your name... Where... you're going to
recite it for us here, right?

194
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

195
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:23,000
De ka. Kî ji we ra hazir dike ew e?
 
Go on. Who prepares it for you?

196
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,000
Na. Kêşka gundî (keçika gundî).
 
No. The village girl.

197
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:28,000
Kê dest pê kirî? Wê ji te ra hazir dikir?
 
Who started it? She was preparing it for you?

198
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:30,000
Wê li me girtî bû.
 
She gave it to us.

199
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:31,000
Makê te?
 
Your mother?

200
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

201
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,000
Ka navê xwe carekê bêje.
 
Come on, tell your name once.

202
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Te got ez Ereb im ne?
 
You said I am Arab, right?

203
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,000
Na, navê te çi bû?
 
No, what was your name?

204
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,000
Ramî.
 
Rami.

205
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,000
Ramî. Navê te çi pêk hatî dest pê kirî?
 
Rami. How did your name come about?

206
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Ha? Eslê min gundî yakî me.
 
Huh? I am originally from this village.

207
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,000
Navê makê te?
 
What is your mother's name?

208
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,000
Ê, ji ser gundî yakî me.
 
Well, I am from this village.

209
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,000
Baş e. Ka dê bibêjî ne?
 
Alright. Are you going to recite it?

210
00:10:46,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Ka dest pê bike.
 
Go ahead, start.

211
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:56,000
De ka zivire vê derê, de were.
 
Come on, turn here, come here.

212
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:59,000
Ka gişt werin, gişt werin.
 
Come on everyone, everyone come.

213
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:03,000
Ka hûn... Ka gişt werin... Were.
 
Come on you... Come on everyone... Come.

214
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:08,000
Ka bizivirin, bizivirin vê derê.
 
Come on, turn around, turn around here.

215
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:09,000
Navê we helbestê tiştek dizanî?
 
Do you know the name of this poem?

216
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:11,000
Na welle... Ez dikarim niha ji we re bibêjim...
 
No, honestly... I can recite it for you now...

217
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,000
Ez dikarim... Hûn hemî guhê xwe bidin min ez ê bibêjim.
 
I can... All of you listen to me, I will recite it.

218
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,000
Dê bê... Ka gişt werin kêleka min bisekinin.
 
Alright... Come on, everyone stand next to me.

219
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:22,000
Gelo navê wî... Wê hemî stranekî bi me re bibêje ne. Ka were
kêleka min. De...
 
Is his name... He is going to sing a song with us. Come next
to me. Go on...

220
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:26,000
Ey reqîb her, maye qewmê kurd ziman
 
O enemy, the Kurdish nation's language remains

221
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Naşikê û danayê bi topê zeman
 
It will not break and will not be defeated by the weapons of
time

222
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Kes nebêje kurd dimirin, kes nebêje kurd dimirin, kurd jîn
dibin, jîn dibe qet nakeve ala kurdan.
 
Let no one say Kurds die, let no one say Kurds die, Kurds
are reviving, reviving, the flag of the Kurds will never
fall.

223
00:12:42,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Yellah bi xatirê we, saetên we xweş.
 
Alright, goodbye, have a good time.

224
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:10,000
Yek ji wan gundên ku em ketin nav malên kevirên reş î de. Û
bi şêwazê malên Osmaniyan hatibû avakirin.
 
One of the villages where we entered the black stone houses.
And it was built in the style of Ottoman houses.

225
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:13,000
Di nav de me gelek alav û lûleyên sifir dîtin.
 
Inside, we saw many copper tools and pipes.

226
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:21,000
Û dîmenekî jiyana kevnar di hişê mirov da çêdike.
 
And it creates a scene of ancient life in a person's mind.

227
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja.
 
Yes, our dear viewers.

228
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:26,000
Îro roja înê ye em derbasî gundê Stêr bûn.
 
Today is Friday, we passed into the village of Ster.

229
00:13:26,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Bi rastî Gundê Stêr jî... me dît ku piraniya xelkê hemî da
ketine kar.
 
Indeed, the village of Ster too... we saw that most of the
people have all fallen into work.

230
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:33,000
Îro în e, dîsa te'tîl nakin. Ji ber ku karê vî gundî pir e.
 
Today is Friday, yet they don't take a day off. Because the
work of this village is plentiful.

231
00:13:33,000 --> 00:13:37,000
Naha jî em derbasî nav baxçeyekî bûn, em ê bipirsin.
 
Now we have also entered an orchard, we will ask.

232
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:42,000
Herin em xwediyê baxçeyê bibînin, em ê bipirsin, çi li vî
gundî diçînin.
 
Let's go see the owner of the orchard, we will ask, what
they plant in this village.

233
00:13:42,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Merheba wextê we baş.
 
Hello, good day to you.

234
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:46,000
Merheba ser çavan we xêr hatin.
 
Hello, welcome upon my eyes.

235
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:48,000
Silav. Em ê te nas bikin.
 
Greetings. We will get to know you.

236
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Mihemed Nûrî ji gundê Stêr, Mihemed Nûrî Hesê jî ji min re
dibêjin. Dibe ku Hesê jî nas nekin, ya.
 
Mihemed Nuri from the village of Ster, they also call me
Mihemed Nuri Hese. They might not know Hese either, you see.

237
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,000
Ser çavan mamê Mihemed.
 
Upon my eyes, uncle Mihemed.

238
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,000
Silav ser çavan, ehlen û sehlen.
 
Greetings upon my eyes, welcome.

239
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,000
Îro em derbasî gundê we bûn.
 
Today we passed into your village.

240
00:13:59,000 --> 00:14:02,000
Û bi rastî me dît ku hemî milet da ketibû kar îro.
 
And indeed we saw that the whole nation had fallen into work
today.

241
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Te'tîl nakin roja înê.
 
They don't take a day off on Friday.

242
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:09,000
Rast e. Yanî kar pir e. Du şuxil in, în be, yekşem be...
 
That's right. I mean, there is a lot of work. There are two
tasks, whether it's Friday or Sunday...

243
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:14,000
Em diqetînin, wextê betlaneyê tuneye ji me re. Xêr e, karê
me pir e.
 
We finish it up, there is no vacation time for us. Goodness,
our work is a lot.

244
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:18,000
Zîreata me... me girtiye vî derî, av heye, zevî hene. Yanî
şixulê me li vê derê pir e.
 
Our agriculture... we've taken up this area, there is water,
there are fields. So our work here is plentiful.

245
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,000
Hûn çi diçînin?
 
What do you plant?

246
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:26,000
Welle patatan nuha diçînin, berê pembû bû, naha muameleyê
dewletê hatin girtin.
 
Well, potatoes we plant now, it used to be cotton, now the
state's procedures have been blocked.

247
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:29,000
Patatan diçînin, pîvazan diçînin.
 
They plant potatoes, they plant onions.

248
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:34,000
Xidre (şînkayî) bacan e... Çi xidre hebe em gişt diçînin. Çi
cûreyî hebe...
 
Vegetables, eggplants... Whatever vegetables there are, we
plant them all. Whatever type there is...

249
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:37,000
Yanî ne bes darê zeytûna ye ne, hemî fêkî, hemî tişt...
 
So it's not just olive trees, right, all fruits, all
things...

250
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:40,000
Xidre, xidre... Erê erê xidre, em gişt diçînin. Çi cûreyî
hebe...
 
Vegetables, vegetables... Yes yes vegetables, we plant them
all. Whatever type there is...

251
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:42,000
Erdê me pir e. Yanî pir in, xurt in.
 
We have a lot of land. I mean it's plenty, they are strong.

252
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:46,000
Erdê me pir giran (bi qîmet) e, ev inteca (berhema) xwe baş
e.
 
Our land is very valuable, its production is good.

253
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Înşelah ev berhema xwedê bi me re daye wê pir derkeve.
 
God willing this harvest that God has given us will come out
plenty.

254
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,000
Ba fêkî jî heye?
 
Is there fruit as well?

255
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:52,000
Fewake jî heye. Sêv hene, hirmî hene.
 
There is fruit too. There are apples, there are pears.

256
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:58,000
Vê axê we çi tê de biçînî dibe. Çi dar tê de biçînî, ew lê
dibe.
 
Whatever you plant in this soil, it grows. Whatever tree you
plant in it, it grows.

257
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:01,000
Yanî zengîn e axa me pir, pir rind e.
 
I mean our soil is very rich, very good.

258
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Çi ferq di navbera axa we û axa gundên din heye, yanî?
 
What is the difference between your soil and the soil of
other villages, then?

259
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:09,000
Vê derê ava xwe heye. Û axa wê, û axa wê sor e.
 
Here it has its own water. And its soil, and its soil is
red.

260
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Axa sor, te çi tê de çand zû dibe. Yanî tehemmulê dike.
 
Red soil, whatever you plant in it grows quickly. I mean it
bears it well.

261
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:17,000
Û niha, hûn çi diçînin ha te got dema patatan e?
 
And now, what are you planting, oh you said it's potato
season?

262
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Niha patatan, orta vê mehê teqrîben em ê... xilas bikin,
yanî.
 
Now potatoes, around the middle of this month we will...
finish, you see.

263
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,000
Patatan em ê hilbikin.
 
We will harvest the potatoes.

264
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:31,000
Û wekî din jî, xidre berhev dikin, pîvazan... Vê derê pîvaz
in me çandine em ê hilkin, berhev bikin.
 
And besides that, we harvest vegetables, onions... Here are
onions we've planted, we'll pull them up, harvest them.

265
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,000
Naha dema pişt re hûn ê çi biçînin?
 
Now, what will you plant afterwards?

266
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:37,000
Demên pêş de ha ev xilas bê em ê erdên xwe bajon...
 
In the coming times once this is finished, we will plow our
fields...

267
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Û em ê genim biçînin, ceh biçînin.
 
And we will plant wheat, plant barley.

268
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:48,000
Nîsk e, noka ne... em diçînin. Ha weha... Şûnê pir e, şûnê
genim e, me baçê (bêdera) genim rakir xidre çandin.
 
Lentils, chickpeas... we plant them. Like this... There are
many places, there are places for wheat, we harvested the
wheat crop and planted vegetables.

269
00:15:48,000 --> 00:15:51,000
Du mewsima, sê mewsima jî erdê me tîne.
 
Our land yields for two seasons, even three seasons.

270
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:53,000
Yanî hûn hemî debara xwe bi van erdan dikin?
 
So you all make your living off of these lands?

271
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:56,000
Erê, debara gund hemî bi van erdan e.
 
Yes, the village's livelihood is entirely based on these
lands.

272
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:59,000
Gund derdikevin derve? Yanî derkevin derve jî kar dikin?
 
Do the villagers go outside? I mean, do they go out to work
too?

273
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,000
Wellehî ha li bal... ewên derve ne jî...
 
Well, those... who are outside too...

274
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:07,000
Lê em, xwediyê der û berê xwe, em dibin Efrînê, ew... Bazara
me... Firotgeh... tenê Efrîn e.
 
But we, owners of our surroundings, we take it to Afrin,
that... Our market... The market... is just Afrin.

275
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:16,000
Na behsa... Mesele ez wiha dibêjim, min dît ku me çend gund
dîtin... Diçûn li Efrînê kar dikirin. Ê gundê we ji derkevin
derva kar bikin?
 
No regarding... For example I'm saying this, I saw that we
saw some villages... They used to go work in Afrin. Does
your village go out to work?

276
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,000
Welle hinekî...
 
Well, a little...

277
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:27,000
Yanî hejmarek pir kêm çûne... Berê em... ev tiştê me li vira
rind in em ê çima herin Efrînê û Helebê? Kar li wir nakin.
Tirkiyê ji... du sê mal çûne.
 
I mean a very small number went... Back then we... these
things are good here so why would we go to Afrin and Aleppo?
We don't work there. To Turkey too... two or three families
went.

278
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Şixulê me li vê derê rind e, baş e.
 
Our work here is good, fine.

279
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:36,000
Yanî berhem pir e û pere jî tê re heye. Mirov bi şixul e,
şixulê Tirkiyê li vir bike du deh saetan wê bixebite lê vê
derê sibê heya êvarê.
 
So production is plenty and there is enough money. A person
has work, doing the work of Turkey here they would work ten
hours but here it's morning till evening.

280
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:47,000
Telefonkirin jî hewce nake tu bi telefonê bigerî. Ev lî vê
derê em bi malî dixebitin, mesele vedihêsin, rûdinên, bi
telefonê diaxivin... Çar pênc saetan dixebitin.
 
You don't even need to call around on the phone. Here we
work as a family, for example they rest, they sit, they talk
on the phone... They work four or five hours.

281
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:51,000
Ji ber ku xwediyê kar e. Kengî dilê wî xwest vedihêse kengî
xwest jî kar dike.
 
Because he is the owner of the work. Whenever he wants he
rests, whenever he wants he works.

282
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:54,000
Erê rast e, her weha. Rast e.
 
Yes, that's right, exactly like that. Right.

283
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:57,000
Naha te got pîvazan li vir digirin ne? Erê.
 
Now you said they harvest onions here right? Yes.

284
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:17,000
Kerem ke em derbasî wê derê jî bibin em dîtina pîvazan jî
nîşanî we bidin çawa ye. Kerem kin hevalno.
 
Please let's pass over there too, let's show you what
harvesting onions looks like. Come on, friends.

285
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:40,000
Em li gund digeriyan, em rastî vê koma karkeran jî hatin. Em
ê hinekî bi wan re jî bipeyivin...
 
We were walking around the village, we also came across this
group of workers. We will talk to them for a bit...

286
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:42,000
Merheba xwîşkno.
 
Hello, sisters.

287
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,000
Ehlen wa sehlen.
 
Welcome.

288
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Qewet be xwîşkê.
 
Strength to you, sister.

289
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,000
Silametî. Hûn xêr hatin.
 
Peace. Welcome.

290
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:46,000
Merheba dayê.
 
Hello, mother.

291
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:47,000
Ehlan.
 
Hello.

292
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,000
Saetên we xweş. Xwedê qewetê bide we.
 
Have a good time. May God give you strength.

293
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,000
Ji we re jî.
 
To you too.

294
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:51,000
Dayê tu ji Gundê Stêr î?
 
Mother, are you from the village of Ster?

295
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:53,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

296
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,000
Naha hûn saet çendê vê sibê hatin?
 
What time did you come this morning?

297
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:58,000
Vê sibê lew em saet şeşan hatin e.
 
This morning... we came at six o'clock.

298
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:00,000
Saet şeşan hûn hatin. Heta kengî hûn dixebitin?
 
You came at six. Until when do you work?

299
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:04,000
Heta... em şeş saetan dişuxulin heta dudu û nîvan.
 
Until... we work for six hours, until half past two.

300
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:09,000
Xwedê saetên we xweş bike. Dema we xwarin xwar hinekî din?
Yan hûn herin malê?
 
May God make your time pleasant. Did you eat something else
later? Or do you go home?

301
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:11,000
Em ê xilas bikin, em ê herin mal.
 
We will finish and go home.

302
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:15,000
Ê dayê, tu kîjan ciyan jî tu diçî kar dikî? Hema ji vî karî
re?
 
So mother, where else do you go to work? Just for this work?

303
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Em xwediyê kar in. Ev karê me bi xwe ye. Em gişt ji gund in.
 
We own the work. This is our own work. We are all from the
village.

304
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,000
Hemî ji gund in, ne?
 
Everyone is from the village, right?

305
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:22,000
Em gişt li gund rûdinin. Em bi malbata xwe xwediyê kar in...
 
We all live in the village. As a family, we are the owners
of the work...

306
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:25,000
Em tenê ji wir hiltînin, em dixin tûran, û em ê bibin sûkê
(bazarê) û em ê bifroşin.
 
We just pick it up from there, put it in bags, and we will
take it to the market and sell it.

307
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,000
Ê dayê... Çend zarokên te hene?
 
So mother... How many children do you have?

308
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:30,000
Ê min... Deh heb hene.
 
I have... ten.

309
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:31,000
Xwedê ji te re bihêle.
 
May God spare them for you.

310
00:18:31,000 --> 00:18:32,000
Ji te re jî bihêle.
 
May He spare yours too.

311
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Zarokên te tu yeko bi te re nehatiye?
 
Did none of your children come with you?

312
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:38,000
Naha Çar... Çar hatine.
 
Now four... Four have come.

313
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,000
Kanîna? Kîjan in... Kîjan zarokên te ne?
 
Where are they? Which ones... Which ones are your children?

314
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:46,000
Yek e ew e ha, yek jî li wê derê... kuro çûn ha... Erê gişt
keç in...
 
One is that one, and one is over there... boys they went...
Yes, they are all girls...

315
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:48,000
Xwedê ji we re bihêle.
 
May God spare them for you.

316
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:54,000
Ka em derbasî, hinekî dî jî bibin...
 
Let's pass over, be a bit more...

317
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:55,000
Silav. Merheba dayê.
 
Greetings. Hello, mother.

318
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,000
Ehlen we sehlen.
 
Welcome.

319
00:18:56,000 --> 00:19:00,000
Qewet be xwişkê... Saetên we xweş. Tu ji kê derê yî?
 
Strength to you, sister... Have a good time. Where are you
from?

320
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:03,000
Xwedê te jî xweş bike qurban... Em jî ji Kurdistana Sûriyê
ne qurbanê, ez a Kurdistanî me.
 
May God make you pleasant too, my dear... We are also from
Syrian Kurdistan, my dear, I am a Kurdistani.

321
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,000
Dayê karekî zexmet e? Zexmet e, ne?
 
Mother, is it difficult work? It's difficult, isn't it?

322
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:09,000
Ne, zexmet nîne. Zexmet nîne, em mecbûr in... ev rîzqa me
ye... û em fîqîr in... em ê bixebitin.
 
No, it's not difficult. It's not difficult, we are
obliged... this is our sustenance... and we are poor... we
have to work.

323
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Dinê germ e... Şikir elhemdulîllah. Havîn e, germ e, weke
havîn bihar, zivistan... payîz e. Karê me ye... patat in,
pîvaz in, û weke mîna van we dîtiye... Berhemên dar û beran,
pembo... ewê dibe, em wisa kar dikin û ji rîzqa xwe razî ne.
 
The weather is hot... Thanks be to God. It is summer, it is
hot, like summer, spring, winter... it's autumn. This is our
work... potatoes, onions, and things like what you see...
The fruits of the trees and plants, cotton... whatever there
is, we work like this and are content with our sustenance.

324
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:35,000
Qewet be ji we re, dayê. Tu bi tenê hatî... zarokên te bi te
re hene...
 
Strength to you, mother. Did you come alone... do you have
children with you...

325
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:44,000
Qîzeke min yek li malê ye. Û ez li vî pîvaza ha ha...
dixebitim. Dixebitim...
 
One of my daughters is at home. And I am working... on these
onions. I am working...

326
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:50,000
Kulfetên min îşa... deh sal e miriye, ez jî xwediyê pênc
zarokan im dayê...
 
My husband passed away... ten years ago, I am taking care of
five children, dear...

327
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:55,000
Û ji bo van da em diherin... Şivan in, yan jî derdikevin
dervayî wî karî bikin...
 
And because of them we go... They are shepherds, or they go
out to do other work...

328
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,000
Tiştek bi dest me nakeve.
 
We don't get anything.

329
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Ê dayê... Min navê te nepirsî?
 
So mother... I didn't ask your name?

330
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,000
Hûn rojane li vir çiqas pere distînin?
 
How much money do you earn here daily?

331
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:08,000
Wellehî yewmiyen, her şexsekî pênc sed e. Em şeş saetan
dişixulin, pênc sed wereqe.
 
Well, daily, for each person it's 500. We work for six
hours, a 500 note.

332
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Baş e, yanî di gundê xwa da bin û ji we ra pênc sed be...
 
Okay, so if you are in your own village and you get 500...

333
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:16,000
Erê baş e di gundê xwe de, em tên şixulê xwe, em diherin
mala xwe nav qeçkê xwe.
 
Yes, it is good to be in our own village, we come to our
work, we go back to our home among our children.

334
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:20,000
Kesî xerîb bi me re tune. Em gî cîran in, gî wek xuşk û bira
kanî bi hev re.
 
There are no strangers among us. We are all neighbors, all
like sisters and brothers together.

335
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:24,000
Ê Xwedê we ji hev ra bihêle... serkeftin ji we ra.
 
May God keep you together... success to you.

336
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:28,000
Sehlan, ehlen û sehlen. Em bi qurbana Kurdistana xwe bin,
qurbana axa xwa bin.
 
Welcome, hello and welcome. May we be the sacrifice of our
Kurdistan, the sacrifice of our land.

337
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:40,000
J'axa xelkê çêtir e.
 
It's better than other people's land.

338
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:45,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja, naha em ji nav erdê pîvaza
derketin, me berê xwe da vir jî.
 
Yes, our dear viewers. Now we have left the onion field, we
headed this way as well.

339
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:49,000
Me dît hinek li vir jî rûniştin e û lîstikek xweş çêkirin e
ji xwe ra.
 
We saw that some people are sitting here too, and they are
playing a nice game for themselves.

340
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,000
Me got em silavê lê bikin û bidin wan, em hinekî pê re
sohbet bikin.
 
We said let's greet them, and let's have a little chat with
them.

341
00:20:51,000 --> 00:20:53,000
Tembûr jî dest xwe kirîye.
 
He also has a tembur in his hand.

342
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:56,000
Ka em silavê bidin wan û nas bikin. Merheba ji we re.
 
Let's greet them and get to know them. Hello to you.

343
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,000
Ehlen û sehlen. Ehlen we sehlen heval.
 
Welcome. Welcome, friend.

344
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,000
Xwe nas bike ji min re.
 
Introduce yourself to me.

345
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,000
Welleh ez Zekî me, ji gundê Stêr.
 
Well, I'm Zekî, from the village of Stêr.

346
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:02,000
Ser çavê min.
 
You are very welcome.

347
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,000
Sax bî.
 
Thank you.

348
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:06,000
Tu b'xwe ji gundê Stêr î û niha li vir hûn çi karî dibînin?
 
You yourself are from the village of Stêr, and what kind of
work are you doing here now?

349
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:10,000
Welleh li vir a, em tên nav erdê xwe, me ev holik çêkiriye.
 
Well, here, we come to our fields, we've set up this hut.

350
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:16,000
Û em tên mûameletê xwe ra dikin, derdê xwe ra dikin. Mûsaede
dikin, derdikin... Em tên rûdinin.
 
And we come to sort out our affairs, share our troubles. We
help out, we go out... We come and sit.

351
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:20,000
Û carna li tembûrê dixin, û carna kilama dibêjin.
 
And sometimes play the tembur, and sometimes sing songs.

352
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,000
Yanî ew kar dikin, tu jî stranan dîbêjî ji wan re?
 
So they work, and you sing songs for them?

353
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:24,000
Erê, ez jî stranan dibêjim.
 
Yes, I also sing.

354
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,000
Ê çi karî dikin?
 
And what kind of work do they do?

355
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Pîvaza, welleh pîvaza hildikin, axşîvê dikin... filan dikin
bexşa çi be.
 
Onions, well, they pull out onions, they clear weeds... they
do this and that, whatever the garden is.

356
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:34,000
Baxçan da diçînin.
 
They plant in the gardens.

357
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:37,000
Xwedê we ji hev ra bihêle... Naha hûn wekî kar stran jî
dibêjin?
 
May God keep you together... Now, you also sing as a job?

358
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:42,000
Naha jî em sekiniyene em bêsînin, di nav re li tembûrê dixim
ew jî kêf xweş dibin.
 
Now we are also taking a break to rest, occasionally I play
the tembur and they get happy too.

359
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:46,000
Ez tam weke hesta xwe dibînim.
 
I see this exactly as my feeling.

360
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:51,000
Çi qasî xweş e. Me re li ser xatirê karkeran jî li tembûrê
xîne stranekê bêje.
 
How nice. So play the tembur and sing a song for the sake of
the workers for us.

361
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Tamam, tamam. Herê.
 
Okay, okay. Yes.

362
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,000
Naha wê tu çi bêjî?
 
What are you going to sing now?

363
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,000
Welleh çi daxwaz kin ez ê bêjim.
 
Well, whatever they request, I'll sing.

364
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:58,000
Beriya naha wan ji te çi dixwestin caran?
 
What did they use to request from you before this sometimes?

365
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:04,000
Welleh klamê tiştê edî dîrok, dera ev Xelîl Xemgîn, kîjan
dilde hate evan ra ez dibêjim.
 
Well, the historical things, from Xelîl Xemgîn, whatever
comes to heart for them, I sing it.

366
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:05,000
Û naha wê em çi strangê bibîhîsin?
 
And what song are we going to hear now?

367
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:09,000
Naha em carna dîsa klamekî jê bêjin, dîsa çi daxwazên wan
bin carê ez ê bêjim.
 
Now we sometimes sing a song from it again, again whatever
their request is, I will sing it.

368
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:11,000
Ka kerem ke yekê ji me re bêje.
 
Please go ahead and sing one for us.

369
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:12,000
Sax bî, ehlen we sehlen.
 
Thank you, welcome.

370
00:22:12,000 --> 00:22:22,000
Lê lê dayê ez binalim zêna xwe didim çiyan…
 
Oh mother, I moan, I turn my face to the mountains…

371
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:28,000
Bi mij û dûman e…
 
It is misty and smoky…

372
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:34,000
Bi mij û dûman e…
 
It is misty and smoky…

373
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:40,000
Lê lê dayê sewda serê min
 
Oh mother, the passion in my head

374
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:48,000
Fîrgeran e, fîrgeran e
 
Is spinning, is spinning

375
00:22:48,000 --> 00:23:08,000
Dermanê dilê min î dayê ronîya çavê min î oyyy
 
You are the medicine of my heart, mother, the light of my
eyes, oyyy

376
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:33,000
Lê lê dayê ez vê ketim welleh te xerîb û xurbetê
 
Oh mother, I have fallen, by God, into foreign lands and
exile

377
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:43,000
Bê mecal û zor e... Bê mecal û zor e...
 
Without power and it's hard... Without power and it's
hard...

378
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:50,000
Lê lê dayê te ji pîşa çavê min
 
Oh mother, from in front of my eyes

379
00:23:50,000 --> 00:24:10,000
Dûr e... lê lê dûr e...
 
It is far... oh it is far...

380
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:54,000
Te dît e, te dît e rinda min te dît e...
 
You saw, you saw my beautiful one, you saw...

381
00:24:54,000 --> 00:25:01,000
Te dît e, te dît e rinda min te dît e...
 
You saw, you saw my beautiful one, you saw...

382
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:09,000
Ji qerqaşê te b' xwedê min xêr nedît e
 
From your snow-white (skin), by God, I have not seen any
good

383
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:16,000
Min xêr nedît e
 
I have not seen any good

384
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:24,000
Waaay way way way qederê
 
Waaay way way way destiny

385
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:31,000
Waaay way way way qederê
 
Waaay way way way destiny

386
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:51,000
Ketme serê milê qatnayî derê
 
I fell onto the folded shoulder of the door

387
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:37,000
Çi gundek î dorketê da, çi gundek î dorketê da
 
What a village in the surroundings, what a village in the
surroundings

388
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:48,000
Mala rindê di warê te da, gulek sor e
 
The beautiful one's house is in your territory, a red rose

389
00:26:48,000 --> 00:27:00,000
Minî tê da, min xwestî bo lo gundî nadan...
 
In it, I asked for her, oh the villagers didn't give her...

390
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:08,000
Waaay way way way qederê
 
Waaay way way way destiny

391
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:14,000
Ketme serê milê qatnayî derê
 
I fell onto the folded shoulder of the door

392
00:27:14,000 --> 00:27:16,000
Her bijî heval... spasiya te dikim.
 
Long live, friend... thank you.

393
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:17,000
Sax bî heval.
 
Thank you, friend.

394
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:35,000
Şêniyên gundê Stêr wekî piraniya gundên kantona Efrînê,
debara xwe ji çandiniyê wekî zeytûn, mêwe, û xwedîkirina
sewalan pêk tînin.
 
The residents of Stêr village, like the majority of the
villages in the Afrin canton, make their living from
agriculture such as olives, fruits, and raising livestock.

395
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:42,000
Belê temaşevanên me yên hêja, di gund da ji gotin sê kanî li
vir hene. Û sê aş li vir hene.
 
Yes, our dear viewers, in the village they said there are
three springs here. And there are three mills here.

396
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:46,000
Me got em ê derbasî ser vî kaniyê bibin wê aşnasî bikin,
kaniyên din jî germ e.
 
We said we will go to this spring and get to know it, the
other springs are warm.

397
00:27:46,000 --> 00:28:06,000
Me got em destpêkê ava van ji kaniyê vexwin, paşê em dê
derbas bin seknek li vir e, em dîroka kaniyê jî bipirsin.
 
We said let's drink water from the spring first, then we'll
move on to a stop here, and ask about the history of the
spring too.

398
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:15,000
Temaşevanên me yên hêja bi rastî avek xweş e, avek pir hênik
e.
 
Our dear viewers, it is truly beautiful water, very cool
water.

399
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:19,000
Ev xweşbûna gund da ye. Ev xwezayiya gund da ye.
 
This is the beauty in the village. This is the nature in the
village.

400
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:39,000
Min dîtî av dherike, milêkî bîstan e, milêkî fêkî ye.
Xwezayiya gund ev e. Ev xweşikbûna gund a ye.
 
I saw water flowing, on one side is an orchard, on one side
is fruit. This is the nature of the village. This is the
beauty of the village.

401
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,000
Selam û eleykum.
 
Peace be upon you.

402
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,000
Eleykumselam. Merheba ji we re.
 
And peace be upon you. Hello to you.

403
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,000
Merheba, xweş hatî.
 
Hello, welcome.

404
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:05,000
Ehlen wa sehlen.
 
Welcome.

405
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,000
Ehlen wa sehlen bi we.
 
Welcome to you.

406
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:08,000
Merheba ji we re.
 
Hello to you.

407
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:16,000
Ehlen we sehlen.
 
Welcome.

408
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:17,000
Merheba ji we re.
 
Hello to you.

409
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,000
Ehlen.
 
Welcome.

410
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:20,000
Em we nas bikin.
 
Let us get to know you.

411
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:23,000
Ehlen wa sehlen. Navê min Mihemed e xalê we.
 
Welcome. My name is Mihemed, your uncle.

412
00:29:23,000 --> 00:29:28,000
Ser çavê me Apê Mihemed. Em we jî nas bikin?
 
You are very welcome Uncle Mihemed. Let us get to know you
too?

413
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:32,000
Merheba, ehlen we sehlen, merhebteyn. Navê min Mihemed Elî
Ehmed.
 
Hello, welcome, double hellos. My name is Mihemed Elî Ehmed.

414
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:37,000
Navê min Îbrahîm e, Fetah, ji gundê Stêr.
 
My name is Îbrahîm, Fetah, from Stêr village.

415
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:40,000
Ser çavê min. Apê Mihemed emriyê te çiqas e?
 
You are very welcome. Uncle Mihemed, how old are you?

416
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:44,000
Emriyê min ha 85 in, teweldê min 31 in.
 
My age is 85, my birth year is '31.

417
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:46,000
Xwedê emrekî xweş bide te.
 
May God give you a good life.

418
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:51,000
Sax bin, xwedê ji te razî be.
 
Thank you, may God be pleased with you.

419
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:56,000
Apê Mihemed li vira sê kanî hene, sê aş hene...
 
Uncle Mihemed, there are three springs here, there are three
mills...

420
00:29:56,000 --> 00:30:00,000
Em derbas bûn me hinek ji ava kaniyê jî vexwar.
 
We passed by and drank some of the spring water too.

421
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:03,000
Kanîyeke pir xweş e, hênek e.. sar be.
 
It is a very beautiful spring, it's cool.. it's cold.

422
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:04,000
Me dîtin ji viraştir, me go em silavke bidin we û..
 
We saw you from a bit further away, we said let's give you a
greeting and..

423
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:06,000
Ehlen û sehlen.
 
Welcome.

424
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:08,000
Sax bî. Tu li vir çi şixulî dibînî? Çi karî dikî?
 
May you be healthy. What are you doing here? What work are
you doing?

425
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:12,000
Ez li vira, bes li vira me.
 
I am here, just here.

426
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:13,000
Tu şivantiyê dikî?
 
You are shepherding?

427
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:14,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

428
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:15,000
Jiyana şivantiyê xweş e ne?
 
The life of shepherding is nice, isn't it?

429
00:30:15,000 --> 00:30:16,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

430
00:30:16,000 --> 00:30:19,000
Apê Mihemed, tu tiştkî li ser vê kaniyê zanî?
 
Uncle Mihemed, do you know anything about this spring?

431
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,000
Tiştkî çawa zanim?
 
Like what do I know?

432
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:26,000
Yanî dîrok.. dîrok, kîjan wextê ev kaniye li vir çêbûne? Ev
sê aş in ha!
 
I mean history.. history, when was this spring built here?
These are three mills you know!

433
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:29,000
Welle, ev zêdeyî sed salî ye.
 
By God, this is over a hundred years old.

434
00:30:29,000 --> 00:30:35,000
Yanî, ne gihaştibûmê.. berê de ev ha.. çêkirine ev aş ha.
 
I mean, I hadn't reached it (wasn't born yet).. long ago
this.. they built this mill.

435
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:38,000
Sed sal, hey! Ser sedsalekî re.
 
A hundred years, yes! Over a century.

436
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:39,000
Tu behsa aşî dikî?
 
You are talking about the mill?

437
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:41,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

438
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:43,000
Aş bû, yê millete me bû.
 
It was a mill, it belonged to our people.

439
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:48,000
Vê re digotin Aşê..
 
They used to call it Mill of..

440
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:50,000
Çoqê.
 
Çoqê.

441
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,000
Ev aşê di nav de li vir..
 
This mill inside here..

442
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:53,000
Ê Çoqê.
 
Of Çoqê.

443
00:30:53,000 --> 00:30:56,000
Nexwe her kaniyeke aşek li ber bû?
 
So every spring had a mill in front of it?

444
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:59,000
Ê lê, erê.
 
Yes, indeed.

445
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:02,000
Waha jêrî jî dîsa kaniyek li ber bû..
 
Down there too, there was another spring with one in front
of it..

446
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:05,000
Vê re digotin Aşê Corc.
 
They used to call it Corc's Mill.

447
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:07,000
Ew jî yê gundê Stêr bûn?
 
Did that also belong to the village of Stêr?

448
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:09,000
Erê. Ev aş jî yê gundê Çoqê.
 
Yes. This mill also belongs to the village of Çoqê.

449
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,000
Ê Çoqê.
 
Of Çoqê.

450
00:31:10,000 --> 00:31:12,000
Erê..
 
Yes..

451
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,000
Ê tê bîra te..
 
So do you remember..

452
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:19,000
... te jî yê ku ser gel e, me jî hinekî pê re ...
 
... you who are over the people, we also a little bit with
this ...

